==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strontia
<hw>Stron"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>strontia</ets>, fr. <ets>Strontian</ets>, in Argyleshire, Scotland,
where <ets>strontianite</ets> was first found.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An earth of a white color resembling lime in appearance, and baryta
in many of its properties. It is an oxide of the metal
strontium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strontian</ent>⟦br⟧
